Ofcourse the message here is &#x27;too much abstraction&#x27;.<p>There are loads of bad frameworks that want to be too smart and too clean. I mean, there is nothing wrong with writing HTML. But I&#x27;ve seen stuff like:<p><pre><code>   $output .= $framework->dom->returnInputElement(&#x27;text&#x27;, &#x27;name&#x27;, $initValue, $options);
</code></pre>
That&#x27;s nice and all but when it just returns the element without any extra functionality I think its just a waste of code and resources.
